- the L<sw-ex>or</sw-ex>ds of the treasury went that day

up a greate on many vessells in the River Seisne and King James is expected there the beginning
of 140000<sw-sup>l</sw-sup> per Ann<sw-ex>um</sw-ex> till the money Charged

able by parliam<sw-ex>en</sw-ex>t the remainder being
40000<sw-sup>li</sw-sup> shall be a fund to raise 300000<sw-sup>li</sw-sup>

Cent for 2 Livre more --
yesterday a Comittee of
Councill Satt where greate number of
O<sw-ex>u</sw-ex><sl>r</sl> protestants appeard one p<sw-ex>ar</sw-ex>t Complaining
ag<sw-ex>ain</sw-ex>st the other for not Justly distributing

their hands : both partys were heard
and their L<sw-ex>ord</sw-ex><sw-ex>shi</sw-ex>ps tooke time to Consider
thereon The office which was secretary
Trenchards is fitting up for the L<sw-ex>ord</sw-ex> of
Shrewsbury the former being to Atend
Since my last wee have
rec<sw-ex>eive</sw-ex>d Letters from Dublin of the 18 past
which say that the L<sw-ex>or</sw-ex>d Capell one of the
L<sw-ex>or</sw-ex>d Justices of Irel<sw-ex>an</sw-ex>d who was left very
sick the last post is p<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>fectly recoverd - that
a greate many vessells are Lading with
Corne in Sev<sw-ex>er</sw-ex>all ports of the K<sw-ex>ing</sw-ex>dome to saile
for England that divers Jennies & west
India Shipps are arrivd at Kinsale - that
S<sw-ex>i</sw-ex><sl>r</sl> Cyrell with one of the L<sw-ex>or</sw-ex>d Justices --
will be made a Lord Chamberlaine in roome
